Case called at 8:45 am [Clerk SH]
[Reserve Judge Mark Frankel presiding for BrIV]
Defendant Sabrina K Street in court with Attorney Yelena Olegovna Zarwell. ADA Monica J. Hall appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
On Motion of the State, the Court AMENDS Count #2 to Disorderly Conduct, contrary to 947.01(1), a Class B misdemeanor 
On Motion of the State, the Court ADDS Count #4, Disorderly Conduct, contrary to 947.01(1), a Class B misdemeanor

Constitutional rights given; plea of "No Contest" entered on Counts #2 & #4; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders JOC entered.

On Counts #2 & #4, the Court withholds sentence, places Defendant on Probation for 1 year, each count, concurrent, with conditions:
--Write a letter of apology to the Principal of Jefferson High School and submit it to her Agent within 45 days of disposition of case
--To undergo any assessment, treatment or counseling as required per Agent
--To attempt to obtain/maintain employment and/or education program, per Agent
--No presence at the Jefferson High School, unless approved by Agent
--No acts/threats of violence
--To complete 40 hours of community service only if available
--To pay costs of $486 ($243 each count)
--To pay $400 DNA Surcharge ($200 each count)
--To pay $33 subpoena fees

Days credit for time already served: 0 days
Court presents basis and grants expungement upon successful completion of probation
